# Google Sheets Database Integration
# 
# To set up Google Sheets as your database:
# 
# 1. Create a new Google Sheet with these tabs:
#    - "providers" - Service provider data
#    - "problems" - Pollution problems data
#
# 2. In the "providers" tab, add headers in row 1:
#    id | name | service | rating | reviews | estimate | specialties | responseTime | availability | email | phone | location | experience | certification | insurance | portfolio | successRate
#
# 3. In the "problems" tab, add headers in row 1:
#    id | title | location | latitude | longitude | severity | category | description | reportedBy | reportedDate | status | priority | estimatedCost | deadline | images | tags
#
# 4. Make your sheet publicly viewable (Share > Anyone with the link > Viewer)
#
# 5. Copy your sheet ID from the URL:
#    https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/[YOUR_SHEET_ID_HERE]/edit
#
# 6. Add the sheet ID below:

NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_SHEETS_ID=your_sheet_id_here

